Lateral aspect of podosoma
: Genal tooth broad, subrectangular, with dens ventrodistally, with longitudinal ridge ventrally (
Fig. 19B
). Tutorium about 120 µm long of, which cusp about 72 µm long, rectangular; distal margin variable, with distinct dorsal and ventral dens (
Fig. 19B
), or with 6–10 dens along anterodorsal and distal margin. Custodium about 29–40 µm long, tapered (
Fig. 16
). Porose area Al about 11 µm in diameter.

Development of leg setae is similar to that given for 

Oribatella canadensis
(
Behan-Pelletier & Eamer 2010
)

